sentences: Born in Vienna, she grew up in Lwów, where she lived with her parents and brothers until 1943.
After the outbreak of World War II, she remained in Lwów and was arrested there along with her mother in 1943.
She performed in the Birkenau camp orchestra until October 1944 then she was evacuated to Ravensbrück and than Neustadt-Glewe, where she was liberated in 1945.

She died on June 12, 2018 at the age of 102.

sentences: Helena Dunicz-Niwińska (July 28, 1915 – June 12, 2018) was a Polish violinist, translator and author.
She started playing the violin at the age of ten in the Lwów conservatory of the Polish Musical Society and continued with pedagogical studies undertaken in the years 1934–1939.
In October of the same year she was deported to the Auschwitz-Birkenau concentration camp.

Together with the orchestra, she performed both during the daily camp events and on special evening concerts for SS personnel, where the works of Edvard Grieg, Robert Schumann and Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart were performed.
